        "subject": "LU-5628 build: undefine macro to avoid conflicts with kernel",
        "message": "LU-5628 build: undefine macro to avoid conflicts with kernel\n\nWhen building Lustre client on a kernel which has already merged\nLustre client codes, there will be definition conflicts between\nkernel and external Lustre codes. This patch undefines existing\ndefiniton of kernel in config.h to avoid this problem.\n\nSigned-off-by: Li Xi <lixi@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: If07644b5a913b2727306ac8207eec9653965be4c\n"
      },
